# EyeCare — Download & Install

Reduce eye strain by filtering blue light and controlling screen brightness. This page explains how to install EyeCare from GitHub Releases (without source code).

## Quick Install (Windows)

1. Go to the repository’s “Releases” page.
2. Download the latest installer:
   - eye-care-Setup.exe — recommended
   - eye-care-Win.zip — portable (no install)
3. Run `eye-care-Setup.exe` and follow the installer prompts.
4. Launch “EyeCare” from the Start Menu or Desktop shortcut.

### Portable ZIP (no install)
- Unzip `eye-care-Win.zip` to a folder you control (e.g. `C:\Apps\EyeCare`).
- Double‑click `EyeCare.exe`.
- To remove, delete the folder.

## System Requirements

- Windows 10 or later
- 64‑bit OS
- Standard user permissions (admin not required for normal use)

## Using EyeCare

- Display page:
  - Adjust Warmth (color temperature)
  - Adjust Brightness
  - Presets: Health, Office, Reading, Game, Movie, Editing, Custom
- Day/Night:
  - “Day” sets light mode + bright preset
  - “Night” sets dark mode + warmer preset
- Activate:
  - “Activate” turns on the screen overlay filter

## Keyboard Shortcuts

- Ctrl + Alt + F — Toggle overlay filter on/off
- Ctrl + Alt + D — Open Display page
- Ctrl + Alt + S — Open Settings page

## Uninstall

- Installed via EXE:
  - Open “Add or remove programs” (Settings → Apps)
  - Find “EyeCare” and click Uninstall
- Portable ZIP:
  - Close the app and delete the folder

## Troubleshooting

- Overlay not visible:
  - Press Ctrl + Alt + F to toggle
  - Ensure no other overlay apps are running
- Styles look plain:
  - Restart the app; ensure you downloaded the latest release
- Antivirus warnings:
  - The app is packaged with Electron; allow it if flagged
- App won’t launch:
  - Reboot Windows, then reinstall the latest release

## Privacy & Permissions

- EyeCare does not collect or transmit personal data.
- No special permissions are required; overlay runs on top of the screen only.

## Support

- Open an Issue on GitHub with:
  - Windows version, EyeCare version (from Releases)
  - What you tried, and a screenshot if possible

